&gt; improper error handling can cause a full back trace to be displayed on-screen,

That&#39;s a very proper concern. 

However, the solution is very simple 

- in order to avoid displaying *any* errors on-screen, just tell PHP to do so, setting `display_errors` configuration directive to 0.
- in order to avoid leaking the database credentials into a stack trace (even if not displayed, getting into the logs is not much better), just catch the exception and throw a brand new one as it will effectively erase the stack trace and create a new empty one, just like it shown in my article, [How to connect with PDO](https://phpdelusions.net/pdo_examples/connect_to_mysql)

Basically you need

    try {
